    {
      "type": "contrast_example",
      "content": "In this second poem, **せ (se)** is the Mizenkei form of our auxiliary. Notice the pattern: **[Noun/Stem] + も (mo) + せ (se)**. This is a common logical structure in classical poetry to say 'Neither X-ing [nor Y-ing]'. Here, 'se' is the 'Action Driver' that turns the state of 'waking' (oki) or 'sleeping' (ne) into an active process that is then negated."
    },
